// Performace and Best Pratices with Constructors

let apple = new String("apple");
apple; // --> {"apple"}

//the apple variable is an object of type string

// How the apple object differs from the following pear variable.

let pear = "pear";
pear; // --> "pear"

//the pear variable is a stron literal, that is a primitive JavaScript value.
//the pear variable, being a primitive value, will always be more performant that apple variable, which is an objec

